		<description>Hi Christopher,
We don't know each other. I was referred to your website by (Col.) Jim Williams. Jim and I have served together on the board of the Intercultural Cancer Council for more than 10 years. I just wanted you to know that I'm a survivor of three different primary cancers. I was given five years to live and on May 22, 2009, I'll celebrate my 23rd year of survival. God is good and prayers are powerful. I will be praying daily for you and your family. I, too, was misdiagnosed with my second cancer, allowing it to metastasize to many places. It's been almost nine years since that time and I'm cancer free. Hang tough and never give up. I'm in Jacksonville, Florida and will be here cheering you on.

Keep the faith.

Bobbi de Córdova-Hanks</description>
